    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
   <style type="text/css">
    

    
    .purplebox {
		background-color:#B404AE;    
    }
    
 	.bluebox {
		background-color:blue;    
    }
    
   
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<p> Apart from predefined color like red,blue,green etc we can use specific colors. Each color has a hash code in html using that has code we can change to that particular color. For color has code <a href="http://www.html-color-codes.info"> click here.</a></p>

Syntax :<br />
background-color:#B404AE<br />
example :<br /><br />

&nbsp&nbsp&lthtml><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lthead><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&ltstyle type="text/css"><br /><br />
    
    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    .purplebox {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp		background-color:#B404AE;<br />    
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    .bluebox {<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    background-color:blue;<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp    }<br /><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/style><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/head><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&ltbody><br /><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt div class="bluebox"><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&ltp style="color:#FFFF00"> This is yellow color text in blue box. &lt/p><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/div><br /><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt div class="purplebox"><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp This a div with purplebox style class<br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/div><br /><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&lt/body><br />
&nbsp&nbsp&lt/html><br /><br />

output : <br />
<div class="bluebox">
<p style="color:#FFFF00"> This is yellow color text in blue box. </p>
</div>
<div class="purplebox">
 This a div with purplebox style class
</div><br /><br />

